g.text: Schema for validating response objects from Integrations when streaming events as agents.
The status of the response. Should always be 'success' or 'error'.
A unique identifier for the invocation, formatted as a UUID.
The event ID, should be a non-negative integer, starting from 0.
Indicates whether this is the final event in the sequence.
A list of response objects containing message and type.
The message object containing details of the response.
Name of the agent providing the response.
Input provided to the tool by the agent.
Log of the actions taken and observations made.
Observations made by the agent after performing the action.
